videos.headline: Georgia Tech coughs up ball on opening drive
videos.description: Yellow Jackets RB KirVonte Benson rushes right, but has the ball poked loose by Clemson's Kendall Joseph and the Tigers recover.

videos.headline: Cain breaks free to put Clemson on the board
videos.description: The Tigers strike first as Kelly Bryant connects with Deon Cain who sheds a defender and scores from 38 yards out.

videos.headline: Yellow Jackets force Tigers fumble
videos.description: Clemson's Travis Etienne rushes for 7 yards before Antonio Simmons rips the ball away and Georgia Tech's Shep Durham falls on it to force the turnover.

videos.headline: Benson rips off huge run to put Georgia Tech deep in Clemson territory
videos.description: KirVonte Benson barrels through the line of scrimmage and gets all the way down to the Tigers' 9-yard line for a 65-yard gain.  The drive would result in a Yellow Jackets field goal.

videos.headline: Clemson's Bryant tosses second TD of first quarter
videos.description: Kelly Bryant connects with Milan Richard in the end zone for a 20-yard score, giving Bryant his first career game with multiple passing touchdowns.

videos.headline: Etienne pounds it in to extend Clemson lead
videos.description: Travis Etienne jumps into the end zone to score from 2 yards out, giving the Tigers a 21-3 lead.

videos.headline: Johnson: 'We're screwing ourselves' in first half
videos.description: Trailing 21-3 going into the half, Georgia Tech coach Paul Johnson is disappointed with his team's effort, saying the Yellow Jackets must execute better if they want a chance to win.

videos.headline: McCloud refuses to go down as Clemson enters Georgia Tech territory
videos.description: Kelly Bryant completes a short pass to Ray-Ray McCloud who sheds several Yellow Jacket defenders en route to a 22-yard gain, setting up a Tigers field goal.

videos.headline: Clemson D-Line 'swag surfin' during timeout
videos.description: Leading 24-3 in the third quarter, the Tigers' defensive line has some fun, breaking into a rendition of the "swag surfin" dance.

videos.headline: Yellow Jackets air it out for fourth down conversion
videos.description: On fourth-and-six, TaQuon Marshall rolls right and connects with Ricky Jeune along the sideline for a gain of 23 yards and a first down.

videos.headline: Marshall scampers in for Georgia Tech TD
videos.description: Yellow Jackets QB TaQuon Marshall uses his legs to scramble in for a touchdown, scoring from 22 yards out.

videos.headline: Clemson handles Georgia Tech in the rain
videos.description: Kirk Herbstreit and Chris Fowler break down the Tigers' 24-10 win over the Yellow Jackets, citing Clemson's dominant defensive effort as the reason for the victory.

videos.headline: Swinney: 'Good teams respond'
videos.description: Coming off a shocking loss to unranked Syracuse, Clemson coach Dabo Swinney lauded the play of the team's defense and QB Kelly Bryant in the Tigers' 24-10 win over Georgia Tech.

videos.headline: Bryant: 'I felt really good out there'
videos.description: Clemson QB Kelly Bryant says he felt good physically against Georgia Tech as he continues to recover from an ankle injury and a concussion.

videos.headline: Clemson defeats Georgia Tech
videos.description: No. 7 Clemson cruises past Georgia Tech 24-10 thanks to Kelly Bryant's 207 passing yards.
